rComments: The online course was pleasant. Clear due dates, and lots of help were offered.

I had him for 19B and 23A. He was very clear and organized. He went over proofs when introducing things more than other professors I've had for lower division math classes. He's enthusiastic about the material. A very good professor.

Had him for 19A, 19B in the 2013-2014 year. Took him again this past quarter for the online version of 23A. The class seemed to be, for the lack of a better word. unfinished. Alot of the homeworks didn't have solutions, and the material got much harder towards the end. Also doesn't curve, which was suprsing, because he does in 19A and 19B

I took Math 19A fall quarter and it was online. It was a good class because you could re-watch all the videos. But since he explains the concept so well, I only watched it once. The midterm was so easy that I got a 105% (due to extra credit). I would recommend taking this fall quarter where it is online.

NEVER TAKE THIS ONLINE! It's a trap, the lectures were horrible, the homework was incredibly long and hard for no reason. The book was confusing and barely any help was offered. I wish I didn't take this class. Did I mention the lecture Sucked, they were filled with useless info on the history of math and mathematical mistakes.

You will get the grade you want if you read the textbook and do the work. I thought the videos were pointless because the examples from the book were more thorough. Overall easy class if you have taken calculus before.

Took the Online course, spent pretty good time on homework and studying for the midterm and final. Midterm was easy just know the formulas final was much harder. Go to the final review given by the better ta essential to doing good on the final. Never saw his videos learned everything from the textbook

Great class all quarter. Great quizzes, great review sessions, and easy to understand homework questions. Pretty easy all quarter except the final. Unlike the midterm, the practice test for the final was not like the final exam.

Bauerle is an absolutely amazing professor. He is most definitely a genius, where I asked him to explain concepts beyond the spectrum of the course during office hours and he could whip out proofs for anything. His lectures are VERY IMPORTANT to go to. He explains the concepts very well and he just sounds awesome when he talks. Also DO HOMEWORK.
His online lectures hurt, prepare to use kahn acadamy

I had him for 19a/b and 23a. His lectures are more theoretical but I think he did well explaining the material.  This class is difficult but if you attend all the lectures, don't get behind, and do the HW you'll pass.  He did a good job helping the class visualize the concepts as well. (suggest taking AMS 10/MATH 21 first if math isn't your thing)

Prof. Bauerle is a very fair teacher. If you read the book, attend section and go to his office hours, you will do just fine in the class. He gave out some extra credit online. The only thing I truly hated about this class that it was online and thus causing the exams to be answer only than truly showing what you know on paper.

Great professor and extremely passionate but he can get sidetracked real easily and you end up not learning much.  Tests are fair, he gives A LOT of homework and sometimes all he goes over in class are proofs so you don't even have an actual numerical example to help you out. He can get sidetracked in office hours too so it's better to see a TA.

Online calculus coursegreat for shy people or people just too busy to deal with going to class everyday. He is helpful in answering questions on Piazza and the videos are very straightforward. Lots of opportunities to raise your grade. Gives you more exam time than you'll actually need. Online homework is very helpful so make sure to do it.
He is very good
His lectures are organized and easy to follow. Tests are fairly easy as long as you did past exams and homework.
Good online class. He has lectures online that helped me with new material. Highly recommend to watch the videos before doing the homework.

Frank is a very good teacher and is very clear. His exams are very fair but the final can be a little difficult than the midterms. I received in both of his math 19 A/B online class. If you do the homework and use the ebook, you can do well in his class. He is approachable and overall, a good professor.

One of the best professors I have ever had. I really struggle with math but I constantly went to class and to his office hours and somehow came away with an A. Its funny because math is my weakness and it is pretty much the only A I have received at UCSC. TOUGH work though. Be dedicated, he wants you to succeed. Very nice professor.
It isnt easy..

This prof is the BEST math prof ive ever had anywhere. he was so clear and nice and he basically spelled out what would be on the tests. he was so good! he dressed up on holloween as the tooth-fairy so you know hes funny, also he wears a train conductors hat everyday.
Frank is the best professor I have had yet.

Great teacher and great class. Exams were extremely fair and the quizzes in sections were cake. The homework online was a bit annoying but it was doable. The only thing I didn't like about him was that he wears socks with sandals every now and then.

Frank is a cool guy - sometimes he makes jokes, but overall the class is boring. The most annoying part about lecture is how much Frank writes on the board. He always writes down the exact textbook definitions (which are long and confusing) of a bunch of arbitrary theorems. Go to section - it helps. But make sure to get a good T.A.
For 19A I think Frank did an excellent job.  He interacts with the students and makes jokes and has a faint accent. He also dedicates a lot of time to helping students outside of class.
He's funny and knows his stuff, definitely my favorite math teacher. really cool guy.
Friendly, funny, and in love with the subject. I wish I had gone to class. Not only would I not have failed, but I would have benefited from a great professor.
nice prof, speaks clear, clean english (WOW) but never changes his pants. oops...
amazing math teacher for upper division classes.
I couldn't understand him at all, he was not helpful and made the course more difficult than it was.  DONT TAKE HIM!!

A wonderful teacher, very eccentric and interested in what he teaches, he loves giving a background about the subject that he is teaching, which he makes pretty interesting, and he makes sure that we understand it, his lectures help a lot with his many examples, and he has fun metaphors to describe math

Love Baurele.  He has a good sense of humor and very good at teaching. Go to lectures they help alot because he gives tons of exanples which he uses sometimes on homework or exams. Go to lecture and study his notes and you'll be fine. Careful of him graphing calculator, he tends to love it and it gets really boring. other than that hes great.
His class was so boring. Fell asleep in class 80% of the time. Homework are easy. Exams are easy if you study the practice midterms (they are VERY similar!). Cool guy I guess.

He is such a great teacher, sit in the front you will get the most out of the class. going to every class is also good too, you'll understand more one the tests. his test are straigh forward, nothing crazy hard, you just gotta know the matrial. :) frank=awesome
frank made lectures on integration captivating. i didn't think that was possible. thanks frank.

This guy is the collest math teahcer ever. Is always making jokes in class and gives very clear lectures. Will be very helpful when needed. Makes you turn in homework online which is sweet. Covers sections well and with examples. Never lets you out early, not even by a couple of seconds, hardly runs over time. If you can take him TAKE HIM!

Clear in his speech, and uses good computer images to help the students visualize ideas. Sometimes he gets carried away with his explanations (everyone already gets it, or should, but he keeps going). Read the textbook, its more helpful than most math texts! Make sure you study old material for the final & go to a final review if possible.
Frank is awesome. 'nough said.
Aced 19A and 19B with Frank.  Quite an easy and understanding teacher.  In fact, the best math teacher in the school in my opinion!
he dressed as the tooth fairy for halloween, totally worth the tuition
Took him for both 12 A and 12B, passionate teacher with reasonable midterm/tests.
He is a great teacher! Very passionate about math and made me passionate about it. He is very helpful and very clear, I wish i had him for all math classes.

I took 19A online w/ Frank's lecture videos & wouldn't have made it through w/o them. Math 19B was one of my favorite classes I've taken here at UCSC. I actually looked forward to going to class even though it was at 8 in the morning. Just go to class & do the hw & you should be fine. Frank is an amazing lecturer & I really loved having him!!!!
Best Math teacher I've ever had.

Bauerle is a great professor, but unless you have a solid foundation in Calculus, I would strongly recommend not taking the online class. The absence of mandatory lectures and sections coupled with the courseload wasn't a great experience. The midterms were also difficult.
I got a bad grade because I was a bad student, but Bauerle is a really good teacher if you actually pay attention to him.
Best Math teacher at UCSC, really explains the concepts well, tests are fair (he gives out practice). The material is hard, but that is just nature of multivariable calc.
His notes in class are very thorough and easy to comprehend. His tests on the other hand aren't that easy, but if you understand the material, they aren't so bad. The whole class is pretty fair.
Frank is one of the best professors I've had at UC Santa Cruz. He is very helpful and more importantly he gets the students involved in his lectures.

Frank is a passionate teacher. Very willing to help you with questions. Go to every lecture and section. It will help a lot. Don't be lazy. Midterm was pretty easy, final was on the difficult side. Not tricky, straight forward. Lecture examples may be confusing at times. As long as you study hard, you should be fine.
Very good teacher who does a great job of explaining things. Midterm/final are hard but reasonable if you aren't lazy.
great class but the exams are impossible.

This class was very hard for me. You should know your definitions because he tests on those too. I would suggest to ask him for help if you don't understand anything. When he teaches, he writes down like theorems and definitions more than he shows examples.
Very passionate teacher. He cares alot about this subject which made the class enjoyable. Midterm was 40% of final grade and Final was 50% so make sure to study. Lectures were clear and focused.

Make sure to write down examples done in class. Almost all the problems from the final were done in his lecture throughout the course. The first midterm was very easy, but the final was much harder. He is very passionate about math.

Never went to class, still pulled a B+ out of the course. Frank's a great teacher and an awesome person as well. His lectures are crystal clear, although I only went to a few. The midterm and final are basically the same thing besides a few problems and homework is super easy. A positive and breezy experience, good luck!
Just an amazing teacher. Enough said.

Frank is absolutely amazing. He explains calculus with a lot of clarity, except during the times when he does the proofs for formulas. However, the things that you need to know are crystal clear. Amazing professor who truly cares about his students. I am not a math person at all but I went to his office hours a lot and attended class and ended up getting an A. He is also so understanding. I got really sick and had to move home and he let me take my final home with me. One of my favorite professors thus far.

He is really enthusiastic about teaching and is more than willing to explain things before/after class and in office hours. His class was hard, I expected a C at best but got a B so my advice would be to understand the concepts and don't just memorize formulas.

He's probably the best math instructor I've ever had. He's easy to understand & breaks down everything for you! His exams are made so he knows you have clear knowledge of the subject, so just do the homework. The only thing I could probably complain about is ALEKS. It's useless & it's worth 10% of your grade! He wears a lot of purple. Super funny.
He told interesting history of mathematics, like Fermat's Last Theorem. However, his midterms are sort of scary.
fun guy```` i like him,,,i won't fall into sleep....helpful.
Bauerle is a great teacher - the lectures were very clear and mildly amusing, enough that I wasn't struggling to stay awake. He even dressed up as Bob Marley for Halloween. awesome~
His lectures are pretty much pointless to go to because he is really just not good at teaching.

He is a very nice guy, buy i felt his randomness distracted from the material. Seems like he drinks too much coffee bc he went super fast in lecturing. Especially for this class, since math 100 is very different  from any other math previousely had.
Tries to make multivariable accessible.  Works for some students, not for me.  Good prof .  Toughness was due to material more than prof.  He is fair.  If you have the chance, try his class!
i just don't know. Best teacher I've had so far at UCSC. Go to his office hours and you'll be amazed at how much you'll understand.

Great math teacher!Even though the class was fundamental review for me, I loved every bit of it.His way of teaching is extraordinary.Very comprehensible teacher.Go to lecture and some sections, you should get an A.

Least I could is to write a good review cause he truly is an amazing instructor. He is very clean and intelligent and very helpful. I can certainly say he's the best Math teacher I have ever had! He wants you to learn and encourages you to learn. Midterms are fair but final was tough! A+ Professor!!

Frank is quite possibly one of the best math teachers I've ever had. He's funny, smart, and extremely helpful. He makes difficult material readily accessible to the less math-inclined. Sections are mandatory. Exams are moderately difficult, but he gives generous curves.

Frank is the man. For reals. My favorite thing about him is the woman's hairclip he wears everyday, but apart from the shallow - he's a killer teacher and exceptionally nice person. Take it with him. His tests are very fair but unfortunately section count for a lot.

FRANK IS AMAZING!!!!!! he is super passionate about the subject and is very interested in the success of his students.  Go to him after you get your test back because the TAs grade harder than he does.  I FREAKING LOVED HIM! if you are gonna take this class TAKE IT WITH FRANK!

Frank goes super fast. Maybe this class was just beyond me, but tests are HARD and going to section/class is always a good idea. You get behind if you don't because of the speed. okay so math is definatly NOT my thing...but frank is SUPER patientttt...this is the second time ive taken the class at UCSC and i came away with a B+..i recommend it...

Frank is awesome! He talks about squirrels (I'm pretty sure he has a squirrel farm or something) and he thinks of cool examples that makes stuff easy to understand. He curves fairly, and as long as you go to lecture and do the homework, you'll do good in his class.

easy to pass, sections mandatory so make sure you have a good TA, online hw tedious sometimes, lectures are really boring and you can get info from the website--i played on my laptop throughout lecture so you don't have to go to a single one. grades on curve + i like his hawaiian shirts and clothing choices. fun to look at, not to listen to.

Very clear and passionate about the subj and the success of his students. i HATE math but he made it a breeze. Pretty cool class. I thought I would get a B then his final was pretty challenging so I got a C+. All his tests are pretty tricky and are sometimes are to study for. He's nice though and expects a lot out of his class.
Great class and professor. Highly recommended for people who are interested in math. You get to prove some cool stuff.

really great professor who obviously cares immensely about mathematics. He is approachable and cares about your success as much as a teacher with 300 students can. TAKE HIM WHENEVER YOU HAVE THE CHANCE.

Excellent math professor. Very insightful teaching style and very approachable in office hours. Put in the necessary amount of work, and you will learn a lot from him.

If you miss two classes in a row you will be behind. attendance is must and if you don't get something make sure u go to office hours. Midterms and final are challenging but if you study they are easily doable. Great teacher and loves math

Frank is just awesome! Although he is tough and extremely fair on the exams, he really wants you to put effort on being knowledgeable of the subject. Thus far, Frank is one of the best math teachers I have ever had!

Very clear and loves his job. He grades VERY fairly and wants everyone to do well. Best math professor i've ever had. Ever.

Excellent math professor, one of the best I've ever had. Extremely helpful and seems to be invested in your success and understanding of math. Also very approachable and understanding. a very good professor.testes are fair and as long as you do the study material you'll be fine. he makes some good jokes. but wish he was more german!!!

Even if you don't go to lecture (notes are all posted online), the tests are very fair. great teaching skills, made me believe I could actually pass my math classes! :-D

i hate math im terrible at it i have to take this class and its somewhat manageable with frank he's really nice and i really could have died in this class and im not. so go frank. do the homework study go to section. youll be ok

very enthusiastic and accessible.

really nice and tries to make things easy to understand

Dr. Frank is an awesome professor. he proves everything he introduces and everything is extremely clear. i got an A by doing his practice midterms/finals and doing a little bit of calculus every day. the tests are very fair and doable. don't ditch this class, frank moves very quickly and you don't want to miss anything he says. trust me.
Best math professor I've ever had. I will leave it at that because I don't want to write an essay about how good he is. The book is also just as good as Frank is, all examples are clear and helpful.

he is very fair with his grading, he's very clear and caring.

Frank Bauerle is so many kinds of cool. He's a brilliant professor, most importantly. He loves math and teaching, his lectures are easy to follow, and he's very personable and friendly. I would recommend anything he teaches 100%.

Professor Bauerle is an excellent instructor. I had him for differential and integral calculus. He is always exceptionally prepared, enthusiastic about the topic, and patient with his students.
